<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-07T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/511:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-07T11:00:00+02:00">April 7, 1934—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 7—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>34. Department’s 20, April 6, 1 p.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d497fn42">Not printed.</note> Export Line accepts reservations on steamer
                                sailing from Izmir declaring steamer will call at that port thence
                                after calling at Marmaris proceeding directly to New York arriving
                                about May 10.</p>
                            <p>Send further telegrams to Istanbul as I am returning tonight.
                                Arrangements here completed.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>